public class OperatorNameProvider
extends ExpressionImpl

This is the base class for all psi elements which are operations and have an operation-sign. It is used to check and find the correct element if we want documentation of an operator like @@@ or /@

Author:
patrick (5/5/13)

Method Detail

isOperatorSign

public boolean isOperatorSign(com.intellij.psi.PsiElement operatorSignElement)
Checks whether operatorSignElement is the correct sign for our operation. Example: You wrote code like a @@ b and you are inside @@@ with the cursor and call QuickDocumentation. Then PsiElement is "PsiElement(APPLY)" and the parent element in the parse tree is an instance of Apply. Now the method checks this and concludes, that @@ is indeed the operator sign to Apply.

On the contrary, say you are beside a comma in the code {a,b,c} then the comma is not the operator sign of List and the function returns false.

Parameters:
operatorSignElement - Operator sign to check
Returns:
true if operatorSignElement is the operator sign of this expression

getOperatorName
